result.name: Golden Gate Restaurant

reviews.text: A Hong Kong styled Cha Chan Teng with its own bakery. Freshly baked buns are produced everyday early in the morning. The milk tea and coffee are freshly brewed as well. Foods are inexpensive and they are all value for money. It also offered breakfast and happy hour menu.

An old-style restaurant that has been opened in Aberdeen for decades. In memory, I have eaten beef fried rice noodles and beef spaghetti here. Quality is quite good. It serves Chinese and Western dishes. Meals are available throughout the day. Customers are mainly local residents. In addition, the restaurant sells its own bread. There are not many choices, but the bread is fresh and baked daily. Unlike other bakeries, the bread sold in this restaurant does not contain many additives. Bread is healthier, I recommend it.
